                <section id="section-1" class="mb-16">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">1. What is Qi Certification?</h2>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">Qi (pronounced "chee") is the global standard for wireless power. It uses inductive charging tech. The <a href="https://www.wirelesspowerconsortium.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-semibold">Wireless Power Consortium (WPC)</a> runs this standard. Qi cert makes sure your chargers work safely with all Qi devices worldwide. For a detailed explanation of the underlying technology, see <a href="/blog/wireless-charging-works" class="text-brandOrange hover:underline font-semibold">How Wireless Charging Works</a>.</p>

                    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">The Qi standard has grown a lot since 2008. Today, it powers over <strong>one billion devices</strong> worldwide. This covers smartphones, earbuds, laptops, and car chargers.</p>

                    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">Qi cert is not optional if you want the Qi logo. It's a strict process that checks safety, cross-device work, and performance. Without proper <a href="https://www.wirelesspowerconsortium.com/certification/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-semibold">Qi cert</a>, you cannot legally use the Qi logo on your products or packing.</p>
                    
                    <div class="bg-brandBlue rounded-2xl p-8 text-white mb-8">
                        <h4 class="font-black uppercase mb-4">Qi Certification Facts</h4>
                        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 text-center">
                            <div>
                                <div class="text-3xl font-black text-brandOrange mb-2">500+</div>
                                <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">Certified Products.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <div class="text-3xl font-black text-brandOrange mb-2">350+</div>
                                <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">Member Companies.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div>
                                <div class="text-3xl font-black text-brandOrange mb-2">1B+</div>
                                <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">Devices Shipped.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">At <a href="/about" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-semibold">WOWOHCOOL</a>, we've helped dozens of brands get Qi certification. Our experience guides you from product design all the way to market-ready certification. We make the process smooth and efficient.</p>
                </section>

                <!-- Section 2 -->
                <section id="section-2" class="mb-16">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">2. Why Qi Certification Matters</h2>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">According to the Wireless Power Consortium (WPC), over 10,000 Qi-certified products have been registered globally.</p>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">Qi certification is essential for any wireless charger entering the global market. Here's why:</p>
                    
                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
                            <h4 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3"><svg class="icon-shield-halved mr-2" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 512 512">
    <path d="M256 0c4.6 0 9.2 1 13.4 2.9L457.8 82.8c22 9.3 38.4 31 38.3 57.2-.5 99.2-41.3 280.7-213.6 363.2-16.7 8-36.1 8-52.8 0-172.4-82.5-213.1-264-213.6-363.2-.1-26.2 16.3-47.9 38.3-57.2L242.7 2.9C246.9 1 251.4 0 256 0zm0 66.8l0 378.1c138-66.8 175.1-214.8 176-303.4l-176-74.6 0 0z" fill="currentColor"/>
  </svg>Safety Guaranteed</h4>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Certified products pass strict safety tests. These include FOD, temperature checks, and EMC testing. Failed chargers can overheat or damage devices. Qi cert protects your customers and your brand.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
                            <h4 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3"><svg class="icon-handshake mr-2" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 576 512">
    <path d="M268.9 85.2L152.3 214.8c-4.6 5.1-4.4 13 .5 17.9 30.5 30.5 80 30.5 110.5 0l31.8-31.8c4.2-4.2 9.5-6.5 14.9-6.9 6.8-.6 13.8 1.7 19 6.9L505.6 376 576 320 576 32 464 96 440.2 80.1C424.4 69.6 405.9 64 386.9 64l-70.4 0c-1.1 0-2.3 0-3.4 .1-16.9 .9-32.8 8.5-44.2 21.1zM116.6 182.7L223.4 64 183.8 64c-25.5 0-49.9 10.1-67.9 28.1L112 96 0 32 0 320 156.4 450.3c23 19.2 52 29.7 81.9 29.7l15.7 0-7-7c-9.4-9.4-9.4-24.6 0-33.9s24.6-9.4 33.9 0l41 41 9 0c19.1 0 37.8-4.3 54.8-12.3L359 441c-9.4-9.4-9.4-24.6 0-33.9s24.6-9.4 33.9 0l32 32 17.5-17.5c8.9-8.9 11.5-21.8 7.6-33.1l-137.9-136.8-14.9 14.9c-49.3 49.3-129.1 49.3-178.4 0-23-23-23.9-59.9-2.2-84z" fill="currentColor"/>
  </svg>Interoperability</h4>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Qi cert makes sure your charger works with all Qi devices. Samsung, Apple, Google, Sony, and more. Your customers expect their new charger to work with their gear. Qi cert guarantees this cross-brand fit.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
                            <h4 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3"><svg class="icon-store mr-2" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 512 512">
    <path d="M30.7 72.3C37.6 48.4 59.5 32 84.4 32l344 0c24.9 0 46.8 16.4 53.8 40.3l23.4 80.2c12.8 43.7-20.1 87.5-65.6 87.5-26.3 0-49.4-14.9-60.8-37.1-11.6 21.9-34.6 37.1-61.4 37.1-26.6 0-49.7-15-61.3-37-11.6 22-34.7 37-61.3 37-26.8 0-49.8-15.1-61.4-37.1-11.4 22.1-34.5 37.1-60.8 37.1-45.6 0-78.4-43.7-65.6-87.5L30.7 72.3zM96.4 352l320 0 0-66.4c7.6 1.6 15.5 2.4 23.5 2.4 14.3 0 28-2.6 40.5-7.2l0 151.2c0 26.5-21.5 48-48 48l-352 0c-26.5 0-48-21.5-48-48l0-151.2c12.5 4.6 26.1 7.2 40.5 7.2 8.1 0 15.9-.8 23.5-2.4l0 66.4z" fill="currentColor"/>
  </svg>Retail Requirements</h4>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Big stores need Qi cert for shelf space. Best Buy, Amazon, Walmart, Target, and Currys. Many platforms will remove non-cert listings. Without Qi cert, you are locked out of top sales channels.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
                            <h4 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3"><svg class="icon-gavel mr-2" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 576 512">
    <path d="M169.6 153.4l-18.7-18.7c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L265.6-25.4c12.5-12.5 32.8-12.5 45.3 0L329.6-6.6c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3L214.9 153.4c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0zM276 211.7l-31.4-31.4 112-112 119.4 119.4-112 112-31.4-31.4-232 232c-15.6 15.6-40.9 15.6-56.6 0s-15.6-40.9 0-56.6l232-232zM390.9 374.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3L505.6 214.6c12.5-12.5 32.8-12.5 45.3 0l18.7 18.7c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.8 0 45.3L454.9 393.4c-12.5 12.5-32.8 12.5-45.3 0l-18.7-18.7z" fill="currentColor"/>
  </svg>Legal Compliance</h4>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Using the Qi logo without cert is trademark theft. It can lead to lawsuits, recalls, and big fines. The WPC monitors the market for fake Qi logo use. They take action against violators.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
                            <h4 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3"><svg class="icon-chart-line mr-2" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 512 512">
    <path d="M64 64c0-17.7-14.3-32-32-32S0 46.3 0 64L0 400c0 44.2 35.8 80 80 80l400 0c17.7 0 32-14.3 32-32s-14.3-32-32-32L80 416c-8.8 0-16-7.2-16-16L64 64zm406.6 86.6c12.5-12.5 12.5-32.8 0-45.3s-32.8-12.5-45.3 0L320 210.7 262.6 153.4c-12.5-12.5-32.8-12.5-45.3 0l-96 96c-12.5 12.5-12.5 32.8 0 45.3s32.8 12.5 45.3 0l73.4-73.4 57.4 57.4c12.5 12.5 32.8 12.5 45.3 0l128-128z" fill="currentColor"/>
  </svg>Consumer Confidence</h4>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Today's savvy buyers look for the Qi logo when shopping. The Qi mark means safe, reliable wireless charging. Using the Qi logo on your products builds trust. It also supports premium pricing.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="bg-brandBlue/5 border-l-4 border-brandOrange p-5 rounded-r-xl mb-6">
                        <p class="text-[11px] font-black text-brandOrange uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">EXPERT INSIGHT</p>
                        <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm"><strong>Nina Nico, Wireless Technology Lead at WOWOHCOOL:</strong> "Qi certification is often the most misunderstood part of bringing a wireless charger to market. Many brands assume it's optional or just a logo, but it is a rigorous engineering process covering safety, efficiency, and interoperability. Working with a factory that has pre-certified platforms can cut the timeline from 16 weeks down to 4."</p>
