                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">8. Common Certification Mistakes to Avoid</h2>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">Based on our work with dozens of brands, here are the most common Qi cert mistakes and how to avoid them:</p>
                    
                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 rounded-r-xl p-6">
                            <h4 class="font-black text-red-600 uppercase mb-2"><svg class="icon-circle-xmark mr-2" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 512 512">
    <path d="M256 512a256 256 0 1 0 0-512 256 256 0 1 0 0 512zM167 167c9.4-9.4 24.6-9.4 33.9 0l55 55 55-55c9.4-9.4 24.6-9.4 33.9 0s9.4 24.6 0 33.9l-55 55 55 55c9.4 9.4 9.4 24.6 0 33.9s-24.6 9.4-33.9 0l-55-55-55 55c-9.4 9.4-24.6 9.4-33.9 0s-9.4-24.6 0-33.9l55-55-55-55c-9.4-9.4-9.4-24.6 0-33.9z" fill="currentColor"/>
  </svg>Mistake #1: Sample-Production Mismatch</h4>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">The #1 cause of cert failure. Test samples must match final units exactly. Small changes like a different MOSFET or coil tweak mean re-testing. Lock your BOM before testing starts.</p>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 rounded-r-xl p-6">
                            <h4 class="font-black text-red-600 uppercase mb-2"><svg class="icon-circle-xmark mr-2" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 512 512">
    <path d="M256 512a256 256 0 1 0 0-512 256 256 0 1 0 0 512zM167 167c9.4-9.4 24.6-9.4 33.9 0l55 55 55-55c9.4-9.4 24.6-9.4 33.9 0s9.4 24.6 0 33.9l-55 55 55 55c9.4 9.4 9.4 24.6 0 33.9s-24.6 9.4-33.9 0l-55-55-55 55c-9.4 9.4-24.6 9.4-33.9 0s-9.4-24.6 0-33.9l55-55-55-55c-9.4-9.4-9.4-24.6 0-33.9z" fill="currentColor"/>
  </svg>Mistake #2: Insufficient FOD Testing</h4>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">FOD is one of the most failed test areas. Test with coins, paper clips, keys, and metal plates at various spots. Don't assume your FOD algorithm works without thorough testing.</p>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 rounded-r-xl p-6">
                            <h4 class="font-black text-red-600 uppercase mb-2"><svg class="icon-circle-xmark mr-2" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 512 512">
    <path d="M256 512a256 256 0 1 0 0-512 256 256 0 1 0 0 512zM167 167c9.4-9.4 24.6-9.4 33.9 0l55 55 55-55c9.4-9.4 24.6-9.4 33.9 0s9.4 24.6 0 33.9l-55 55 55 55c9.4 9.4 9.4 24.6 0 33.9s-24.6 9.4-33.9 0l-55-55-55 55c-9.4 9.4-24.6 9.4-33.9 0s-9.4-24.6 0-33.9l55-55-55-55c-9.4-9.4-9.4-24.6 0-33.9z" fill="currentColor"/>
  </svg>Mistake #3: Underestimating Thermal Design</h4>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Temperature limits are strict —surface must stay under 40°C. Good thermal design needs careful PCB layout, parts, and enclosure. Test thermal performance under worst-case conditions with high heat and full load.</p>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 rounded-r-xl p-6">
                            <h4 class="font-black text-red-600 uppercase mb-2"><svg class="icon-circle-xmark mr-2" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 512 512">
    <path d="M256 512a256 256 0 1 0 0-512 256 256 0 1 0 0 512zM167 167c9.4-9.4 24.6-9.4 33.9 0l55 55 55-55c9.4-9.4 24.6-9.4 33.9 0s9.4 24.6 0 33.9l-55 55 55 55c9.4 9.4 9.4 24.6 0 33.9s-24.6 9.4-33.9 0l-55-55-55 55c-9.4 9.4-24.6 9.4-33.9 0s-9.4-24.6 0-33.9l55-55-55-55c-9.4-9.4-9.4-24.6 0-33.9z" fill="currentColor"/>
  </svg>Mistake #4: Wrong Power Class Selection</h4>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Claiming more power than your product can deliver is a serious violation. Be careful with your power class claim. You can always add higher power modes later.</p>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 rounded-r-xl p-6">
                            <h4 class="font-black text-red-600 uppercase mb-2"><svg class="icon-circle-xmark mr-2" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 512 512">
    <path d="M256 512a256 256 0 1 0 0-512 256 256 0 1 0 0 512zM167 167c9.4-9.4 24.6-9.4 33.9 0l55 55 55-55c9.4-9.4 24.6-9.4 33.9 0s9.4 24.6 0 33.9l-55 55 55 55c9.4 9.4 9.4 24.6 0 33.9s-24.6 9.4-33.9 0l-55-55-55 55c-9.4 9.4-24.6 9.4-33.9 0s-9.4-24.6 0-33.9l55-55-55-55c-9.4-9.4-9.4-24.6 0-33.9z" fill="currentColor"/>
  </svg>Mistake #5: Incomplete Documentation</h4>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">WPC cert needs detailed docs. Include schematics, BOM, firmware version, test notes, and user manuals. Missing or incomplete docs will slow down your review.</p>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 rounded-r-xl p-6">
                            <h4 class="font-black text-red-600 uppercase mb-2"><svg class="icon-circle-xmark mr-2" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 512 512">
    <path d="M256 512a256 256 0 1 0 0-512 256 256 0 1 0 0 512zM167 167c9.4-9.4 24.6-9.4 33.9 0l55 55 55-55c9.4-9.4 24.6-9.4 33.9 0s9.4 24.6 0 33.9l-55 55 55 55c9.4 9.4 9.4 24.6 0 33.9s-24.6 9.4-33.9 0l-55-55-55 55c-9.4 9.4-24.6 9.4-33.9 0s-9.4-24.6 0-33.9l55-55-55-55c-9.4-9.4-9.4-24.6 0-33.9z" fill="currentColor"/>
  </svg>Mistake #6: Ignoring Regional Requirements</h4>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Qi cert is separate from FCC, CE, and RoHS marks. You need both. Plan your timing to align with or come before Qi testing. See our <a href="/blog/certifications-us-eu-guide" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-semibold">US/EU certifications guide</a> for details.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <!-- Section 9 -->
                <section id="section-9" class="mb-16">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">9. Working with China Factory for Certification</h2>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">China is the top maker of wireless chargers worldwide. Working with an experienced <a href="/about" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-semibold">China-based factory</a> can simplify your Qi cert path a lot.</p>
                    
                    <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
                        <h4 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-4"><svg class="icon-check mr-2" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 448 512">
    <path d="M434.8 70.1c14.3 10.4 17.5 30.4 7.1 44.7l-256 352c-5.5 7.6-14 12.3-23.4 13.1s-18.5-2.7-25.1-9.3l-128-128c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.8 0-45.3s32.8-12.5 45.3 0l101.5 101.5 234-321.7c10.4-14.3 30.4-17.5 44.7-7.1z" fill="currentColor"/>
  </svg>Benefits of China Manufacturing for Qi Certification</h4>
                        <ul class="text-slate-600 text-sm space-y-3">
                            <li><strong class="text-slate-900">Pre-cert platforms:</strong> Many Chinese factories, including <a href="/about" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-semibold">WOWOHCOOL</a>, offer products with existing Qi certs. You can white-label or customize them.</li>
                            <li><strong class="text-slate-900">Faster fixes:</strong> In-house prototyping and testing means quick fixes when issues show up.</li>
                            <li><strong class="text-slate-900">Cost cuts:</strong> Making products in China cuts unit costs. This helps offset cert fees.</li>
                            <li><strong class="text-slate-900">Lab links:</strong> Experienced factories already work with authorized test labs. This makes scheduling and contact easier.</li>
                            <li><strong class="text-slate-900">Part sourcing:</strong> Chinese factories have supply ties for Qi-cert parts like TX coils and controllers. Hard to find elsewhere.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <h4 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-4">Key Considerations When Selecting a China Partner</h4>
                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
                            <h5 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Verify Existing Certifications</h5>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Ask for proof of existing Qi certs. Check them in the <a href="https://www.wirelesspowerconsortium.com/products/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-semibold">WPC product database</a>. Request test reports to see their quality record.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
                            <h5 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Understand IP Protection</h5>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Before sharing your specs, make sure NDAs are in place. Work with factories that serve global brands. They understand privacy needs.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
                            <h5 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Clarify Certification Ownership</h5>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Decide if Qi cert will be under your WPC membership or the factory's. For brand-specific cert, you need your own WPC account. The cert must be in your company name.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6">
                            <h5 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Plan for Mass Production Consistency</h5>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Cert is based on test samples. Make sure the factory has strong QC to keep compliance during mass production. Ask for first article reports.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="bg-brandOrange/10 border border-brandOrange/20 rounded-xl p-6 mt-6">
                        <h4 class="font-black text-brandOrange uppercase mb-2"><svg class="icon-handshake mr-2" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 576 512">
    <path d="M268.9 85.2L152.3 214.8c-4.6 5.1-4.4 13 .5 17.9 30.5 30.5 80 30.5 110.5 0l31.8-31.8c4.2-4.2 9.5-6.5 14.9-6.9 6.8-.6 13.8 1.7 19 6.9L505.6 376 576 320 576 32 464 96 440.2 80.1C424.4 69.6 405.9 64 386.9 64l-70.4 0c-1.1 0-2.3 0-3.4 .1-16.9 .9-32.8 8.5-44.2 21.1zM116.6 182.7L223.4 64 183.8 64c-25.5 0-49.9 10.1-67.9 28.1L112 96 0 32 0 320 156.4 450.3c23 19.2 52 29.7 81.9 29.7l15.7 0-7-7c-9.4-9.4-9.4-24.6 0-33.9s24.6-9.4 33.9 0l41 41 9 0c19.1 0 37.8-4.3 54.8-12.3L359 441c-9.4-9.4-9.4-24.6 0-33.9s24.6-9.4 33.9 0l32 32 17.5-17.5c8.9-8.9 11.5-21.8 7.6-33.1l-137.9-136.8-14.9 14.9c-49.3 49.3-129.1 49.3-178.4 0-23-23-23.9-59.9-2.2-84z" fill="currentColor"/>
  </svg>WOWOHCOOL Certification Services</h4>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">We have been WPC members since 2018 with over 50 Qi-cert products. Our <a href="/service" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-semibold">OEM/ODM services</a> include cert help, pre-compliance testing, and full docs support. <a href="/contact" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-semibold">Contact us today</a> to discuss your wireless charger cert needs.</p>
                    </div>
